<p style="text-align:justify;">or conjuror than the others, he is Consulted like an oracle; and if any of the Children or young people, falls dangerously Ill this great personage is desired to baptize them over again, which is the reason that Indians have always several names; and let him have ever so many, he is sure not to escape having a nick name besides.</p>
<p style="text-align:justify;">When any one falls sick among them, his relatives immediately invite all the others that are near at hand to come and conjure the sick person to health again; and in the evening they attend with their drums and medicine Bags, which they open out and spread on a mat before them &#8211; then an oraison is made to each of these simples and carved bits of wood: as soon as their oraisons are done, which sometimes last for an hour or two, they all begin to sing and beat their drums, and make such a confounded noise round their patient, as would make a person that is in health turn sick, instead of</p>

